In this proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump, he recognizes National Adoption Month and celebrates the love and support that adoptive parents and families provide to children. He also acknowledges the courage of birth parents who choose to place their child for adoption. The proclamation emphasizes that adoption is a blessing for all involved, providing relief for birth parents and loving homes for children. It highlights the importance of strong families and communities and calls for support and assistance for families willing to adopt children in need of permanent homes. The proclamation also emphasizes the need to support children in foster care and help them find permanent families. President Trump affirms the value of human life and encourages all Americans to observe National Adoption Month by helping children in need of permanent homes.